          },
          {
            "type": "force_components",
            "id": "F_components",
            "force_id": "main_vector",
            "decompose_axis": "world_xy",
            "origin_body_id": "origin_point",
            "origin_anchor": "body_center",
            "color": "#F59E0B",
            "scale_pixels_per_unit": 8,
            "animate_in_ms": 1200,
            "label_x": "Fx = {horiz} N",
            "label_y": "Fy = {vert} N"
          },
          {
            "type": "annotation",
            "id": "projection_rule",
            "text": "From the arrow's tip,\ndrop a perpendicular to each axis.\nWhere the shadow lands\n— that is the component.",
            "position": {
              "x": 475,
              "y": 110
            },
            "style": "callout",
            "color": "#F59E0B"
          },
          {
            "type": "annotation",
            "id": "diagonal_hint",
            "text": "The original arrow is just\nthe diagonal of the rectangle\nmade by its two components.",
            "position": {
              "x": 475,
              "y": 280
            },
            "style": "callout",
            "color": "#3B82F6"
          }
        ],
        "teacher_script": {
          "tts_sentences": [
            {
              "id": "s1",
              "text_en": "Watch what happens when we draw two perpendicular lines through the point — one along the ground, one straight up."
            },
            {
              "id": "s2",
              "text_en": "From the tip of the arrow, drop a perpendicular onto each line. Two dashed shadows appear."
            },
            {
              "id": "s3",
              "text_en": "Each shadow is called a component. The horizontal shadow tells you how much of the pull moves the trolley forward."
            },
            {
              "id": "s4",
              "text_en": "The vertical shadow tells you how much of the pull is trying to lift it off the ground."
            },
            {
              "id": "s5",
              "text_en": "And the original arrow? It is just the diagonal of the rectangle formed by its components. This is the geometry of resolution."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
