            "text": "ADJACENT to α → horizontal side.\nOPPOSITE to α → vertical side.\nTrigonometry is built\nexactly for this shape.",
            "position": {
              "x": 490,
              "y": 290
            },
            "style": "callout",
            "color": "#10B981"
          }
        ],
        "teacher_script": {
          "tts_sentences": [
            {
              "id": "s1",
              "text_en": "Look closely at the geometry here. The arrow, its two shadows, and the axes form a rectangle. The arrow is the diagonal."
            },
            {
              "id": "s2",
              "text_en": "Now focus on just half of this rectangle — the right triangle sitting on the x-axis."
            },
            {
              "id": "s3",
              "text_en": "The arrow itself is the hypotenuse. The horizontal component is the side ADJACENT to angle alpha. The vertical component is the side OPPOSITE to alpha."
            },
            {
              "id": "s4",
              "text_en": "Why does this matter so much? Because trigonometry is built for exactly this shape. Sine and cosine are about to pop out."
            }
          ]
        }
