            {
              "id": "s1",
              "text_en": "Let us apply this skill to a classic physics problem. A block of mass two kilograms sits on a thirty-degree incline."
            },
            {
              "id": "s2",
              "text_en": "Gravity pulls it straight down. The red arrow shows m g equals nineteen point six Newtons, pointing to the center of the earth."
            },
            {
              "id": "s3",
              "text_en": "The block will slide down the ramp. But here is the question: how much of that nineteen point six Newtons is actually doing the sliding?"
            },
            {
              "id": "s4",
              "text_en": "The answer depends entirely on how we resolve m g. Which pair of axes should we pick? Let us try two different choices and see."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
