              "text_en": "First, try the obvious choice. Resolve m g along the world x axis and the y axis — the axes you already know from the previous states."
            },
            {
              "id": "s2",
              "text_en": "Watch the gray arrows appear. The horizontal component is zero, because m g has no horizontal part — it points straight down."
            },
            {
              "id": "s3",
              "text_en": "And the vertical component just equals m g itself. We have not learned anything new at all."
            },
            {
              "id": "s4",
              "text_en": "So why did this fail? Look at the motion. The block slides ALONG the incline, not vertically. Our axes do not match the motion. That is the whole problem."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
